<docs>
	<doc for="DataGridSortCommandEventArgs.DataGridSortCommandEventArgs">
		<summary>
			<para>Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridSortCommandEventArgs"/> class.</para>
		</summary>
		<param name="commandSource">The source of the command.</param>
		<param name=" dce">A <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridCommandEventArgs"/> that contains the event data. </param>
		<remarks>
			<para>Use this constructor to create and initialize a new
      instance of the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridSortCommandEventArgs"/> class.</para>
			<para>When an instance of <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridSortCommandEventArgs"/> is created by a
   call to this constructor, the following properties are initialized to the
   specified values.</para>
			<list type="table">
				<listheader>
					<term>Property</term>
					<description>Initial Value</description>
				</listheader>
				<item>
					<term> CommandSource</term>
					<description>The value of the <paramref name="commandSource"/> parameter.</description>
				</item>
				<item>
					<term> SortExpression</term>
					<description>The value of the <paramref name="dce.CommandArgument"/>
parameter.</description>
				</item>
			</list>
		</remarks>
	</doc><doc for="DataGridSortCommandEventArgs.CommandSource">
		<summary>
			<para> Gets the source of the command. </para>
		</summary>
		<value>
			<para>The source of the command.</para>
		</value>
		<remarks>
			<para>Use the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridSortCommandEventArgs.CommandSource"/> property
   to get the command source that raises the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid.SortCommand"/>
   event. Because this event is only raised when
   a link is clicked in the header of the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/> control, the
   returned source is a <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridItem"/> that represents the header. This
   property can be used to programmatically control the header.</para>
		</remarks>
		<example>
			<para>The following example demonstrates how to use the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridSortCommandEventArgs.CommandSource"/>
property to programmatically control the header in the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/> control.</para>
			<codelink SampleID="DataGridAllowSorting" SnippetID="1"/>
		</example>
		<seealso cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/>
		<seealso cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid.SortCommand"/>
	</doc>
	<doc for="DataGridSortCommandEventArgs.SortExpression">
		<summary>
			<para> Gets the expression used to sort the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/> control.</para>
		</summary>
		<value>
			<para>The expression used to sort the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/> control.</para>
		</value>
		<remarks>
			<para>Use the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridSortCommandEventArgs.SortExpression"/> property to determine which column
   the user selects to sort the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/> control.</para>
		</remarks>
		<example>
			<para>The following example demonstrates how to use the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridSortCommandEventArgs.SortExpression"/> property to determine which column
   the user selected to sort the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/> control by.</para>
			<codelink SampleID="DataGridAllowSorting" SnippetID="1"/>
		</example>
		<seealso cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/>
		<seealso cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid.SortCommand"/>
	</doc>
	<doc for="DataGridSortCommandEventArgs">
		<summary>
			<para>Provides data for the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid.SortCommand"/> event of the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/> control.
   This class cannot be inherited.</para>
		</summary>
		<remarks>
			<para>When sorting is enabled by setting the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid.AllowSorting"/> property of the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/> control to <see langword="true"/>,
<see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.LinkButton"/> controls are rendered in the header 
   of each column that has the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridColumn.SortExpression"/> property set. (For
   automatically generated columns, the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridColumn.SortExpression"/>
   property contains the same value as
   the data field.) These links allow you to sort the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/> control by the selected
   column. The <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid.SortCommand"/> event is raised when a
<see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.LinkButton"/> 
control is clicked.</para>
			<para>For a list of initial property values for an instance of
<see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridSortCommandEventArgs"/>, see the <see cref="M:System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridSortCommandEventArgs.#ctor"/> constructor.</para>
			<para>For more information about handling events, see <see topic="cpconEventsOverview"/>.</para>
		</remarks>
		<example>
			<para>The following example demonstrates how to specify and code a handler for the
   <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid.SortCommand"/> event to sort a <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/>
   control.</para>
			<codelink SampleID="DataGridAllowSorting" SnippetID="1"/>
			<codelink SampleID="DataGridSortCommand" SnippetID="1"/>
		</example>
		<seealso cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridSortCommandEventHandler"/>
		<seealso cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/>
		<seealso cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid.SortCommand"/>
	</doc>
</docs>
